'''Fort Logan National Cemetery''' is a [[National cemetery]] in [[Denver, Colorado]], U.S.A. Fort Logan was named after Union General [[John A. Logan]], commander of US Volunteer forces during the [[American Civil War]]. It contains {{convert|214|acre|km2}} and has had 95,905 interments through fiscal year 2008.[http://www.cem.va.gov/CEM/cems/nchp/ftlogan.asp][[Image:fort logan national cemetery 3.jpg|thumb|Fort Logan National Cemetery|200px|right|A street in Fort Logan National Cemetery during Memorial Day weekend]]
